{{WikiProject Languages}}
My advice for Wikibooks is that they be more than just phrases, in order to be more useful. Grammatical forms are good to practice phrases with, but perhaps that's not the way this is set up. At least, I suggest that the creator of lists adds some exercises so that students may practice the phrases. Even if we do not add exercises, which at the inefficient level of information may not even be very useful, a way to improve phrases themselves is to turn them into actual usable sentences or parts of sentences, not just individual terms which will obviously already require great knowledge of the language. Therefore, instead of just "bus stop", the phrase might be "Where is the bus stop?" or something to that effect.
I added some of what I was suggesting; however, I am not proficient in Romanian, so I appeal to those who are. P.S. If anyone has found these additions helpful, please let me know. This is based on what works for me and in theory, but feedback is good. --[[User:Tlaxcalli|Tlaxcalli]] ([[User talk:Tlaxcalli|talk]]) 00:57, 17 May 2008 (UTC)

