===== asctime =====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <ctime>
char *asctime( const struct tm *ptr );
</source>
}}

The function asctime() converts the time in the struct 'ptr' to a character string of the following format:

 day month date hours:minutes:seconds year

An example:

 Mon Jun 26 12:03:53 2000

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/clock|clock]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ctime|ctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/difftime|difftime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/gmtime|gmtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/localtime|localtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/mktime|mktime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/time|time]]

