{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Flutterby Bush| type=Magical plant| features=Decorative, shimmering leaves| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Goblet of Fire|''Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire'']]}}
== Overview ==
The '''''Flutterby bush''''', apparently a purely decorative plant, is treasured for its delicate, fluttering leaves that move even when there is no wind, giving the bush a shimmering appearance.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
In [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Harry Potter|Harry's]] fourth year, his class are called upon to prune flutterby bushes in [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic/Herbology|Herbology class]].
Flutterby bushes appear again as decoration at the doorway to [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Places/The Burrow|the Burrow]] just before [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Bill Weasley|Bill]] and [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Fleur Delacour|Fleur]]'s wedding.
