{{Chess Opening Theory/Position|= |Ware Opening| |rd|nd| |qd|kd|bd|nd|rd|= |pd|pd|pd|bd|pd|pd|pd|pd|= | | | | | | | | |= |pl| | |pd| | | | |= | | | | | | | | |= | | | | | | | | |= | |pl|pl|pl|pl|pl|pl|pl|= |rl|nl|bl|ql|kl|bl|nl|rl|= || }}
Black has moved the bishop in order to prevent 3. Ra4; however, 3. Ra3 is now playable. Other options include d4, Nc3, Nf3, and b4.
