==== mktime ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <ctime>
time_t mktime( struct tm *time );
</source>
}}

The mktime() function converts the local time in ''time'' to calendar time, and returns it. If there is an error, -1 is returned.

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/asctime|asctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ctime|ctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/gmtime|gmtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/time|time]]

