==== localtime ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <ctime>
struct tm *localtime( const time_t *time );
</source>
}}

The function localtime() converts calendar time ''time'' into local time. Watch out for the [[C++ Programming/Code/Statements/Functions/Returning Values/Static Return|static return]].

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/asctime|asctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/ctime|ctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/difftime|difftime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/gmtime|gmtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/strftime|strftime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/time|time]]

