==== ctime ====

{{C++ Programming/Syntax|
<source lang=cpp>
#include <ctime>
char *ctime( const time_t *time );
</source>
}}

The ctime() function converts the calendar time ''time'' to local time of the format:

 day month date hours:minutes:seconds year            

using ctime() is equivalent to

<source lang=cpp>
asctime( localtime( tp ) );
</source>

;Related topics: [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/asctime|asctime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/clock|clock]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/gmtime|gmtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/localtime|localtime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/mktime|mktime]] - [[C++ Programming/Code/Standard C Library/Functions/time|time]]

